The consumer group Which? has done much work on this, identifying dozens of products where inflation has been made to "vanish" by scaling back the size of the pack. It found a box of Nestlé's Shredded Wheat cereal, for instance, which suddenly reduced in weight by 10pc but continued to be sold in Sainsbury's at the same, pre-shrink price. Other products from crisps to burgers also suffered cuts to contents – but not prices – in some cases by 24pc.
